cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper deals with optimal planning using learned neural network models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of mixed-integer linear programming (MILP) and constraint generation algorithms suggests a focus on optimization and control (cs.RO and cs.SY). Finally, the mention of planning over long horizons implies a consideration of dynamic systems (cs.DS).
